NPM can only install certain dependencies. In a linux environment, it will be required to follow these steps before running npm install in the root of the project.
0. Install mongodb (sudo apt-get install mongodb)
0a. Start the service (sudo service mongodb start)
1. Install keberos (sudo apt-get install libkrb5-dev)
1a. This may be all that is needed to run the project, if you still have problems continue the following steps. If this works jump to step 6
2. Run command: (sudo apt-get install build-essential)
3. Download python 2.7 (wget http://python.org/ftp/python/2.7.5/Python-2.7.5.tgz)
3a. Extract (tar -xvf Python-2.7.5.tgz)
3b. Navigate to (cd Python-2.7.5)
3c. Run command (./configure)
3d. Run command (make)
3e. Install the compiled python (sudo make install)
4. Set paths to pythong for npm and node-gyp
4a. Run command (node-gyp --python /Python-2.7.5/python)
4b. Run command (npm config set python /Python-2.7.5/python)
5. Install node-gyp globally (sudo npm install -g node-gyp)

======Mongo=====

6. Setup mongodb
6a. sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv 7F0CEB10
6b. echo "deb http://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu trusty/mongodb-org/3.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-3.0.list
6c. sudo apt-get update
6d. sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org
6e. goto the root and do sudo mkdir /data/
6f. goto the root and do sudo mkdir /data/configdb
6g. sudo chown choiceuser /data/configdb


6e. sudo service mongod start

goto /var/log/mongodb/mongod.log and verify that mongo had started.
goto /etc/mongod.conf to configure mongo

Useful info: to stop service use: sudo service mongodb stop and to restart use sudo service mongod restart